1
00:00:08,133 --> 00:00:11,167
<i>Do you think Paolo's slipping
back into his old habits?</i>

2
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:14,433
<i>What if your husband's cheating
again?</i>

3
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:17,200
<i> I hope I'm wrong.</i>

4
00:00:18,300 --> 00:00:19,767
<i> Hello?</i>

5
00:00:19,900 --> 00:00:20,933
<i> Are you at the office?</i>

6
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:22,333
<i>Yeah, I'm at the office.
I'll just finish this,</i>

7
00:00:22,467 --> 00:00:23,567
<i> then I'll call you back, okay?</i>

8
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:25,533
<i>What is Paolo doing at a hotel?</i>

9
00:00:25,667 --> 00:00:27,567
<i>I'm going to find out the truth.</i>

10
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:28,333
<i> What?</i>

11
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:29,733
<i> Paolo?</i>

12
00:00:30,367 --> 00:00:31,600
<i> Hey, wait! Marj!</i>

13
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:36,600
What is it?

14
00:01:37,767 --> 00:01:39,200
Well, there's some deal here.

15
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,833
Actually, several.

16
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:47,400
Paolo sold five units
at Menagerie Manor at a loss.

17
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:50,100
What?

18
00:01:50,233 --> 00:01:51,600
Why would he do that?

19
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:55,133
He's counting on referrals
from those sales.

20
00:01:56,767 --> 00:02:00,000
He's hoping to sell the
remaining units at full price.

21
00:02:02,767 --> 00:02:04,600
That's really risky.

22
00:02:04,733 --> 00:02:06,700
But clever.

23
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:08,633
So what's the problem?

24
00:02:08,767 --> 00:02:11,167
The board didn't approve this.

25
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,267
He did all of this on his own.

26
00:02:17,067 --> 00:02:18,800
You're planning to
bring this up today?

27
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:20,200
I will expose you.

28
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:24,400
I'll show your dad
and the rest of the board

29
00:02:24,533 --> 00:02:26,767
that Paolo gambled
with company money.

30
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:28,700
And by doing that,

31
00:02:28,833 --> 00:02:31,100
he put Torrecampo Realty
at risk.

32
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:36,267
I'm sure everyone's
going to lose trust in him.

33
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,433
And that'll be the end of him.

34
00:02:38,467 --> 00:02:39,733
Exactly.

35
00:02:53,867 --> 00:02:55,400
Dad...

36
00:02:55,533 --> 00:02:56,767
you wanted to see me?

37
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,267
I know what you did.

38
00:03:06,367 --> 00:03:08,267
What exactly
are you referring to?

39
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:11,467
Aldrin told me
about the undisclosed discounts

40
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:14,567
you gave Mrs. Sutherland...

41
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:16,700
and several others.

42
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:23,500
Dad, it was a calculated move
to secure high-value buyers.

43
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,567
Calculated?

44
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:32,667
You sold five units...

45
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:36,900
below market value
without board approval.

46
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:39,933
Are you an idiot?

47
00:03:41,767 --> 00:03:43,333
Dad, I projected recovery.

48
00:03:44,133 --> 00:03:45,300
Those five client...

49
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:50,300
were supposed to bring in
more buyers.

50
00:03:50,433 --> 00:03:51,500
It was strategic.

51
00:03:51,633 --> 00:03:53,967
Well, your strategy
just collapsed.

52
00:03:55,133 --> 00:03:58,333
Your deal with the
discounted prices got leaked.

53
00:04:00,567 --> 00:04:01,467
Now...

54
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,800
every buyer
expects the same thing.

55
00:04:07,533 --> 00:04:09,933
No one wants to buy
a Menagerie unit

56
00:04:10,067 --> 00:04:11,367
at full price anymore.

57
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,500
You tanked the project!

58
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:18,467
What?

59
00:04:19,733 --> 00:04:21,067
Dad...

60
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,900
that was confidential.

61
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:27,033
That wasn't supposed to get out.

62
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,833
How did it leak?

63
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:38,467
You did this!

64
00:04:39,133 --> 00:04:41,000
You. You leaked it!

65
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:42,567
I don't know
what you're talking about.

66
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:44,700
You sabotaged me! You bastard!

67
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:47,100
I don't know
what you're talking about!

68
00:04:48,967 --> 00:04:51,433
Don't blame someone else
for your mess!

69
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:53,733
Get out!

70
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,600
Out!

71
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:18,300
I still can't believe
Aldrin beat me.

72
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,000
Now everyone's going to think
I'm a failure.

73
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:23,400
The board...

74
00:05:23,533 --> 00:05:24,667
the staff...

75
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:28,133
Pao, not everyone
sees you that way.

76
00:05:28,267 --> 00:05:30,267
Can you just calm down?

77
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:33,167
I don't think you're a failure.

78
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,300
You did everything you could.

79
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:38,733
I know I did.

80
00:05:38,867 --> 00:05:40,600
But it still wasn't enough.

81
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:42,467
I did everything right.

82
00:05:43,533 --> 00:05:45,233
I thought it through.

83
00:05:45,367 --> 00:05:46,567
I took the risk.

84
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:48,000
Gambled with it.

85
00:05:49,267 --> 00:05:51,900
But with just one move
from Aldrin,

86
00:05:52,033 --> 00:05:53,433
it's all over.

87
00:05:55,567 --> 00:05:58,400
Can you just breathe
for a second?

88
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:00,967
I've got you.

89
00:06:02,767 --> 00:06:04,767
Let me help you shake off
that bad mood.

90
00:06:25,867 --> 00:06:29,267
<i>Do you think Paolo's slipping
back into his old habits?</i>

91
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:33,833
<i>What if your husband's cheating
again?</i>

92
00:06:33,967 --> 00:06:37,533
<i>These days, having evidence
isn't enough, sweetheart.</i>

93
00:06:37,667 --> 00:06:40,367
<i>You have to be smarter than him.</i>

94
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:32,267
I hope I'm wrong.

95
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,600
Girl.

96
00:09:15,733 --> 00:09:17,000
Hey!

97
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:19,100
Are you waiting for a text,
a call, or something?

98
00:09:20,967 --> 00:09:22,867
No. Why?

99
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,567
Because you've been glued
to your phone for a while now.

100
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:31,167
I'm just checking
Paolo's location.

101
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:36,033
Oh my god...

102
00:09:36,167 --> 00:09:41,667
You turned on his location
sharing on social media?

103
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,000
We're at that level now?

104
00:09:46,100 --> 00:09:47,633
Do you think I'm
being paranoid?

105
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:49,533
Not really.

106
00:09:49,667 --> 00:09:52,833
If that's what gives
you peace of mind.

107
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:55,400
Do you think your
husband will find out?

108
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:59,600
If he won't check the settings,
he will not know.

109
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:02,500
And I only tried it this time.

110
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:05,600
And look,
he's just at the office.

111
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:09,400
Maybe I really am wrong.

112
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:12,300
I hope so.

113
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:20,867
Oh, Jobert.
My son is so handsome.

114
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:24,800
Jobert, make sure you do your
best at the outreach later.

115
00:10:24,933 --> 00:10:26,867
And I want you smiling.

116
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,600
Keep smiling all the time,
got it?

117
00:10:30,033 --> 00:10:32,500
Like this, Mom?

118
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:36,000
There you go.
Yes, very good, son.

119
00:10:38,967 --> 00:10:42,367
Jobert, just sit here for a bit.

120
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,433
I'll just grab something, okay?

121
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,700
Yes, Mom. I'll come with you.

122
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:49,267
No, it's okay.
Just stay right here, okay?

123
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,767
I will be right back.

124
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:51,867
Okay.

125
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:01,833
Where is she?

126
00:11:01,967 --> 00:11:04,267
Stay right here.

127
00:11:08,133 --> 00:11:09,600
Are you spying on me?

128
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:10,533
Oh my gosh!

129
00:11:10,667 --> 00:11:11,733
No, no.

130
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:13,833
Why would I spy on you?

131
00:11:13,967 --> 00:11:15,333
Because this isn't
the first time

132
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:18,233
I've caught you watching me.

133
00:11:18,367 --> 00:11:20,833
You're getting way
too paranoid, Evelyn.

134
00:11:20,967 --> 00:11:22,500
Why would I even spy on you?

135
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:24,633
Are you hiding something?

136
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:26,133
No.

137
00:11:26,267 --> 00:11:31,033
So tell whoever sent you
to watch me to back off, okay?

138
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:33,167
Because I'm not doing
anything wrong.

139
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,933
I've got to say,
Jasmine's really impressive.

140
00:11:59,067 --> 00:12:01,367
You wouldn't even know she's
going through something.

141
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,967
She doesn't want
people feeling sorry for her,

142
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:07,467
so she follows everything
the doctor says.

143
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:11,533
And she really wants
to get better.

144
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:12,767
You can see it.

145
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:13,867
She's so brave.

146
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,033
I wonder who she got that from.

147
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,200
Who could it be?

148
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:21,733
All I know is her mom's this
tough Visayan woman.

149
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,267
Of course!

150
00:12:34,267 --> 00:12:36,033
What is it?

151
00:12:36,167 --> 00:12:38,867
Paolo's no longer at the office.

152
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,133
Is he heading home?

153
00:12:40,267 --> 00:12:42,800
He's at Olympo Hotel.

154
00:12:42,933 --> 00:12:44,900
What is Paolo doing at a hotel?

155
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:51,567
Well, sometimes client meetings
happen at hotels, right?

156
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:53,733
Maybe he's just meeting
a client.

157
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:58,867
Marj, meetings happen
at the office.

158
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,500
Or at a restaurant.

159
00:13:01,633 --> 00:13:05,600
But I'm not saying
Paolo's doing anything shady.

160
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:07,700
If you're having doubts,

161
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:10,767
clear it up so you don't start
overthinking.

162
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:16,567
Call him.

163
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:22,000
I don't want
to come off paranoid.

164
00:13:22,167 --> 00:13:25,933
You won't. You're his wife.
You have every right to ask.

165
00:13:34,433 --> 00:13:37,633
Ma'am, can I borrow your card?
Please fill this out, too.

166
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:38,833
Of course.

167
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:40,900
Here.

168
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:02,167
Hello?

169
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:03,133
Love?

170
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:05,333
Hello, love?

171
00:14:05,467 --> 00:14:06,767
Are you at the office?

172
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:11,167
Office. I'm in a meeting.

173
00:14:15,633 --> 00:14:17,700
You're at the office?

174
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:19,633
You don't have
a client meeting outside?

175
00:14:23,467 --> 00:14:25,067
No. Just a lot of paperwork.
I'm here at the office.

176
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:27,133
I'll just finish this,
then I'll call you back, okay?

177
00:14:27,267 --> 00:14:28,600
Okay. Bye.

178
00:14:30,667 --> 00:14:31,767
What did he say?

179
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:43,333
Paolo lied to me.

180
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:45,700
He said he was at the office.

181
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,167
What?

182
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,867
You're feeling restless again?

183
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:05,267
I just don't understand
why he has to lie.

184
00:15:07,967 --> 00:15:09,500
Maybe...

185
00:15:09,633 --> 00:15:12,200
maybe he just doesn't want
me to disturb him.

186
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:15,233
Maybe he doesn't want
me asking about work.

187
00:15:15,367 --> 00:15:16,533
He told me before

188
00:15:16,667 --> 00:15:19,633
that I should just let him be
when it comes to work.

189
00:15:19,767 --> 00:15:22,333
Marj, are you really
going to fool yourself?

190
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:23,767
He's hiding something from you.

191
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:25,067
And chances are,
he's with that woman

192
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,867
he was talking to on the phone.

193
00:15:33,233 --> 00:15:35,467
Hey, hey, hey!
Where are you going?

194
00:15:35,633 --> 00:15:37,167
I'm just grabbing my bag.

195
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:38,733
I'm going to find out the truth.

196
00:15:43,867 --> 00:15:46,700
- Say hi!
- Hi!

197
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:48,467
Say hello!

198
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,100
Hello!

199
00:15:50,233 --> 00:15:51,733
Very good!

200
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:54,833
We're going to teach you
how to...

201
00:15:56,467 --> 00:15:58,633
Our sponsor is here!

202
00:15:58,767 --> 00:16:02,267
None other than
Mrs. Regina Torrecampo!

203
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,100
Let's give her
a round of applause!

204
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:07,400
Hello! Hi!

205
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:09,200
Hi!

206
00:16:09,367 --> 00:16:11,100
Hello!

207
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:16,033
Oh, hello! Hello, hello!

208
00:16:16,167 --> 00:16:21,667
And joining her is one of our
former alumnus and scholar

209
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:25,400
from Learning Hearts.
None other than Jobert!

210
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:27,900
Let's give him
a round of applause!

211
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:31,267
And wave to Jobert!

212
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,933
- Hi!
- Wave, wave!

213
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:37,333
- Very good!
- Hi!

214
00:16:37,467 --> 00:16:38,700
There we go.

215
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:42,700
Another round of applause
for Jobert!

216
00:16:42,867 --> 00:16:45,233
Maybe you'd like to say
something?

217
00:16:51,533 --> 00:16:53,533
Hi!

218
00:16:53,667 --> 00:16:56,567
Hi! Hi, everyone!

219
00:16:56,700 --> 00:17:00,400
I used to go to this school,
too.

220
00:17:00,533 --> 00:17:02,900
Hello.

221
00:17:03,033 --> 00:17:05,333
Jobert, that's enough.
That's enough, sweetheart.

222
00:17:05,467 --> 00:17:07,867
Okay.

223
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,267
Let's go over to the side, okay?

224
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,933
Another happy clap for Jobert!

225
00:17:15,633 --> 00:17:18,600
And for Mrs. Regina!

226
00:17:19,767 --> 00:17:23,800
Kids, who wants prizes?

227
00:17:23,933 --> 00:17:25,267
So we're going to have
some games.

228
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:31,100
Evelyn, I think you should
keep a closer eye on Jobert.

229
00:17:31,233 --> 00:17:36,600
You know, not everyone is used
to sudden bursts of enthusiasm.

230
00:17:36,733 --> 00:17:40,200
So if he has a routine
to help him calm down,

231
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:43,733
like medication
or breathing exercises,

232
00:17:43,867 --> 00:17:45,833
anything that works.

233
00:17:45,967 --> 00:17:47,633
Maybe you should do that
ahead of time

234
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,533
so we don't have any
misunderstandings.

235
00:17:50,667 --> 00:17:53,933
I just don't want
any disruptions.

236
00:17:54,067 --> 00:17:56,167
Especially with the media
around.

237
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:58,800
I'm sure you understand, right?

238
00:18:02,933 --> 00:18:08,200
So let's all thank our sponsor,
Mrs. Regina Torrecampo!

239
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:10,033
Thank you!

240
00:18:10,167 --> 00:18:13,500
- Thank you, thank you.
- Mrs. Regina is so kind.

241
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:18,500
- All right, who wants prizes?
- Yes, thank you.

242
00:18:18,633 --> 00:18:21,767
We're going to play a game
called Color Hunt!

243
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:22,933
Jobert, let's sit down, okay?

244
00:18:23,067 --> 00:18:27,500
You'll look for the colors
I say and touch them.

245
00:18:27,633 --> 00:18:28,967
All right, kids?

246
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:33,267
Okay, time to hunt!
Let's look for colors.

247
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:36,233
Oh, very good!
He really knows his colors!

248
00:18:36,367 --> 00:18:40,700
Okay, touch something white.

249
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,967
Go ahead. Very good!

250
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:47,433
He really knows white.
How about something yellow?

251
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:49,000
Yellow!

252
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:50,400
Very good!

253
00:18:50,533 --> 00:18:53,267
Let's see if you
know your shapes.

254
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:56,500
Touch something brown.

255
00:18:57,767 --> 00:18:59,367
- Color brown.
- Very good!

256
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,233
You'll get a prize later.
Good job!

257
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:04,467
Marj.

258
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:05,733
Marj.

259
00:19:05,867 --> 00:19:08,033
Marj, Marj!

260
00:19:08,167 --> 00:19:10,267
Calm down. Marj.

261
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,567
How are we even going to find
them?

262
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:13,100
What if they've already
checked in?

263
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:15,567
We don't even know
the room number.

264
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:16,933
We'll figure it out.

265
00:19:25,767 --> 00:19:26,867
Paolo?

266
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:27,833
Marj?

267
00:19:30,133 --> 00:19:31,800
Hey! Hey, Marj!

268
00:19:31,933 --> 00:19:33,167
Marj!

269
00:19:33,767 --> 00:19:35,800
Again, huge thanks
to our sponsors

270
00:19:35,933 --> 00:19:38,400
and to everyone
who was part of today.

271
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:40,600
Enjoy!

272
00:19:40,733 --> 00:19:43,067
Enjoy!

273
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:45,800
Ma'am Evelyn, would you
like to help hand these out?

274
00:19:45,933 --> 00:19:46,933
- You can stand next to Jobert.
- Oh, no thanks.

275
00:19:47,067 --> 00:19:48,633
I'll just stay here.

276
00:19:48,767 --> 00:19:52,367
Oh, she's shy. Very low-key.

277
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:54,733
She doesn't like the spotlight.
Right, Evelyn?

278
00:19:54,867 --> 00:19:56,567
Yes.

279
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:57,500
Say thank you.

280
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:03,100
- Butterfly.
- Oh, dear.

281
00:20:03,267 --> 00:20:04,133
I want the butterfly.

282
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:07,633
Oh no,
that's not a real butterfly.

283
00:20:07,767 --> 00:20:09,467
It's not a real butterfly.

284
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:19,633
Are you okay?

285
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:20,067
Where's Ma'am Regina?

286
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,333
There! Miss Regina's there!

287
00:21:21,467 --> 00:21:23,167
- Let's help her!
- Ma'am!

288
00:21:23,300 --> 00:21:24,500
Ma'am! Ma'am, the kids.

289
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:26,467
Someone went down, Ma'am!

290
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,500
Go get them.

291
00:22:17,867 --> 00:22:20,267
Marj. Hey!

292
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,867
- Marj.
- Paolo.

293
00:22:22,867 --> 00:22:24,967
Oh, Marj. You're here, too.

294
00:22:25,100 --> 00:22:26,667
How are you?

295
00:22:29,267 --> 00:22:31,033
I'm okay.

296
00:22:31,167 --> 00:22:32,533
Why are you here, too?

297
00:22:32,667 --> 00:22:34,767
We just ran into each other
in the lobby.

298
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:37,367
You?

299
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:39,667
What are you doing here?

300
00:22:46,867 --> 00:22:50,533
I'll get going, okay?

301
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:53,900
Good luck with your plans.

302
00:22:54,033 --> 00:22:56,333
And thanks for the free coffee.

303
00:22:56,467 --> 00:22:58,233
No, you're welcome,
Mrs. Sutherland.

304
00:22:58,367 --> 00:23:00,033
And thank you, too.

305
00:23:00,167 --> 00:23:01,533
Bye, Marj.

306
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:06,167
Oh, I can walk you out.

307
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:07,667
Oh, really? Sure, sure.

308
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,067
Bye.

309
00:23:13,367 --> 00:23:15,033
Really, Marj?
What are you doing here?

310
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:18,467
How did you know I was here?

311
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:26,733
I turned on the location sharing
on your phone.

312
00:23:27,767 --> 00:23:31,033
I needed to know.
I just wanted to be sure.

313
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:33,867
Why?

314
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,767
Marj, why?

315
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,733
Why did you have to do that?

316
00:23:40,833 --> 00:23:43,333
Why did you have
to mess with my phone?

317
00:23:43,467 --> 00:23:46,333
Because I'm scared, Paolo.

318
00:23:46,467 --> 00:23:49,467
You've been so cold to me
these past few days.

319
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:52,533
You won't talk to me,
you won't even look at me.

320
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:56,400
I thought you were cheating.

321
00:23:57,500 --> 00:23:59,200
So when I got the alert
that you were here,

322
00:23:59,333 --> 00:24:00,867
and you told me
you were at the office,

323
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,533
what was I supposed to think?

324
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:09,367
I didn't tell you the truth

325
00:24:09,500 --> 00:24:12,200
because I didn't want
you to worry.

326
00:24:12,333 --> 00:24:14,867
I've been really overwhelmed
with work problems.

327
00:24:16,767 --> 00:24:20,133
My mind is exhausted.

328
00:24:20,267 --> 00:24:22,333
So I just needed to get out
of there for a bit.

329
00:24:23,767 --> 00:24:25,333
Then why here at a hotel?

330
00:24:25,467 --> 00:24:27,500
Because I wanted some peace
and quiet!

331
00:24:31,133 --> 00:24:33,967
I came here
because I wanted to drink.

332
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:36,367
I wanted to get drunk.

333
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:39,367
I wanted to forget
all my stress.

334
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:41,967
And then I just happened
to run into Mrs. Sutherland.

335
00:24:43,633 --> 00:24:46,267
I didn't even know she
was staying here, too.

336
00:24:47,767 --> 00:24:49,000
But you?

337
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:53,200
You disrespected my privacy.

338
00:24:56,933 --> 00:24:58,800
And you doubted me.

339
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:07,400
- I'm sorry.
- Marj, no.

340
00:25:08,933 --> 00:25:12,667
You know, I never thought
it would come to this.

341
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,833
That you'd use my phone
as your own spy tool.

342
00:25:18,067 --> 00:25:20,500
Marj, you're suffocating me.

343
00:25:20,633 --> 00:25:22,533
You're suffocating me!

344
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:27,133
We'll talk some other time.

345
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:50,100
Were you the one who drove Paolo
to the hotel earlier?

346
00:25:50,233 --> 00:25:52,600
Or maybe he's seeing
another woman?

347
00:25:52,733 --> 00:25:53,667
No, Ma'am.

348
00:25:53,800 --> 00:25:56,033
Sir Paolo has changed
a long time ago.

349
00:25:56,167 --> 00:25:59,267
Ever since you got married,
I haven't seen him fool around.

350
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,933
It's happening again.

351
00:26:01,067 --> 00:26:02,833
Greg is cheating on me again.

352
00:26:02,967 --> 00:26:05,833
But I'm sure she's only
after his money, Yolly.

353
00:26:05,967 --> 00:26:07,900
Do you already know
who she is, Ma'am?

354
00:26:08,033 --> 00:26:10,233
They don't mean for it
to happen, right?

355
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,367
What if things just really
happen?

356
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:14,467
Sometimes feelings

357
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:18,000
just come out of nowhere,
even if you didn't invite them.

358
00:26:18,133 --> 00:26:19,167
Maybe they're just being weak.

359
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:23,067
They're cheating on me
in our own home!

360
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:25,233
Dad, is this true?

361
00:26:25,367 --> 00:26:27,433
She was the one
flirting with me.

362
00:26:30,633 --> 00:26:33,267
I rejected her advances.
